messages.content: What is the purpose of the ComfyUI GetFileNameFromURL custom node?
The ComfyUI GetFileNameFromURL custom node is designed to extract the filename from a given URL.
Can the GetFileNameFromURL node handle redirects?
Yes, the GetFileNameFromURL node is capable of handling 303 redirects.
What are the steps to install the GetFileNameFromURL node in ComfyUI?
To install the GetFileNameFromURL node, navigate to the custom_nodes directory of your ComfyUI installation in the terminal, clone the repository using the 'git clone' command, and restart ComfyUI.
What inputs does the GetFileNameFromURL node accept?
The GetFileNameFromURL node accepts a single input: url (STRING), which is the URL from which the filename will be extracted.
What outputs does the GetFileNameFromURL node produce?
The GetFileNameFromURL node produces two outputs: filename (STRING), which is the extracted filename, and url (STRING), which is the input URL.
What would be the output for the input 'https://example.com/path/to/file.jpg' in the GetFileNameFromURL node?
For the input 'https://example.com/path/to/file.jpg', the GetFileNameFromURL node would output the filename as 'file.jpg' and the URL as 'https://example.com/path/to/file.jpg'.
What are the dependencies of the GetFileNameFromURL node?
The GetFileNameFromURL node has two dependencies: 'requests' and 'cgi'.
